@{u}Requirements@{uu}

- An Amiga 8)

- A File with loads of tons of Cookies

- A Mailreader
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "CookieFile"
@prev "Requirements"
@{u}Usage@{uu}

from CLI: @{b}SelectCookie@{ub} NAME <Cookiefile> M=MARK <String>

             NAME : The name of the file which contains the Cookies
             MARK : A String which seperates the Cookies. Default is '%%'.

 To stop @{b}SelectCookie@{ub} from doing whatever it is just doing,
just send him a Break [CtrlC or Kitkat :)].
@endnode

@node "CookieFile" "CookieFileFormat"
@next "Revision History"
@prev "Usage"
@{u}CookieFileFormat@{uu}

 Well, at first, your Cookiefile should start with 1 up to n lines of
seperationmarks. Then there should be cookies [Gen:1,2-3] each 
one seperated with a similar [not the same ;)] mark. At the end,
well there should be one final seperationmark.

And now to something completely different, an example:

%% 
%% 
this is the first cookietext
%% 
hello, i am the second cookie in this examplefile and nobody knows,
why all lines in this file are lowercase ;) 
%% 
windows. [hahahahahahaha...] 
%% 
my brain hurts 
%% 
Hi! I am the last cookie in this Example, and don`t ask Me, 
why my Lines aren`t all lowercase. 
%%


If you follow the rules above, there should never be difficulties.

...Well, not really never. It`s just very likely, that no error will occur.

...And to be honest, there could be an error, I haven`t seen yet.

...Okay, Okay, it is always possible to have difficulties!
@endnode

@node "Revision History" "Revision History"
@next "Bugs"
@prev "CookieFile"
@{u}Revision History@{uu}
@font xen.font 9


0.1     13-Dez-94       @{b}SelectCookie@{ub} gets alive as an ARexx-Script for GoldED
                        to add Cookies at the end of a Script. [2 sec/Cookie out of a
                        2 MB Cookiefile!] I started to puzzle over the meaning of
                        'Random' and its brutal reality :(
0.2     21-Dez-94       Transfered the ARexx-Script into E to be used from
                        CLI as required by IntuiNews.
0.3     24-Dez-94       Celebrating XMas in Bavaria with my relatives. Thought
                        about inserting a special ChristmasCookie 8).
0.4     28-Dez-94       Added the possibility to define your own seperating
                        string.
0.5     31-Dez-94       Cheerio Folks. Hicks. Hihihi 8*).
0.6     01-Jan-95       Uhhh. My Head! Could you speak a little bit softer.
0.7     02-Jan-95       Got Sedgewick`s 'Algorithms'. Added a REAL! Random-
                        function.
0.8     14-Jan-95       Fixed the 32Bit-Border by developing my own Random-
                        function.
1.0     17-Feb-95       Release to the WORLD :).
                        May the Force be with @{b}SelectCookie@{b}.
@endnode

